16 (a) It is the policy of the State:
17 (1) to provide for fair housing throughout the State to all, regardless of
18 race, color, religion, sex, familial status, national origin, marital status, sexual orientation,
19 gender identity, disability, source of income, or military status; and
20 (2) to that end, to prohibit discriminatory practices OR ACTS THAT HAVE
21 A DISCRIMINATORY EFFECT, REGARDLESS OF INTENT, with respect to residential
22 housing by any person, in order to protect and ensure the peace, health, safety, prosperity,
23 and general welfare of all.
24 (b) This subtitle:
25 (1) is an exercise of the police power of the State for the protection of the
26 people of the State; and
27 (2) shall be administered and enforced by the Commission and, as provided
28 in this title, enforced by the appropriate State court.
